    "monster4948": "<h1 class=monster>Elder Brain<br><span class=type>Large aberrant magical beast (blind)</span><br><span class=level>Level 23 Elite Controller<span class=xp> XP 10200</span></span></h1><table class=bodytable><tr><td><b>HP</b> 436; <b>Bloodied</b> 218<td class=rightalign><b>Initiative</b> +17<tr><td><b>AC</b> 37, <b>Fortitude</b> 33, <b>Reflex</b> 35, <b>Will</b> 37<td class=rightalign><b>Perception</b>+19<tr><td><b>Speed</b> 2, teleport 6<td class=rightalign>Blindsight 10<tr><td colspan=2><b>Immune</b> blinded, gaze<tr><td colspan=2><b>Saving Throws</b> +2; <b>Action Points</b> 1</table><h2>Traits</h2><p class='flavor alt'>☼ <b>Warp Reality</b> ✦ <b>Aura</b> 5</p><p class=flavorIndent>Any enemy that teleports while within the aura takes 10 damage. </p><p class='flavor alt'> <b>Absorb Thoughts</b> </p><p class=flavorIndent>Whenever a nonminion ally within 10 squares of the elder brain drops to 0 hit points, the elder brain makes a saving throw or a power recharge roll. </p><p class='flavor alt'> <b>Unseeing Telepathy</b> </p><p class=flavorIndent>The elder brain can communicate with other creatures telepathically even if it does not have line of effect to those creatures.</p><h2>Standard Actions</h2><p class='flavor alt'>(⚔) <b>Tentacle Warp</b> (teleportation) ✦ <b>At-Will</b></p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Attack:</i> Melee 3 (one creature); +26 vs. AC</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Hit:</i> 1d8 + 8 damage. The elder brain teleports the target 3 squares, and the target is immobilized until the end of the elder brain's next turn.</p><p class='flavor alt'>⚔ <b>Flailing Warp</b> ✦ <b>At-Will</b></p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Effect:</i> The elder brain uses tentacle warp three times, making each attack against a different target.</p><p class='flavor alt'>ᗕ <b>Mind Burst</b> (psychic) ✦ Recharge ⚄ ⚅</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Attack:</i> Close burst 5 (enemies in the burst); +27 vs. Will</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Hit:</i> 3d8 + 6 psychic damage, and the target is dazed (save ends).</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Miss:</i> Half damage.</p><h2>Minor Actions</h2><p class='flavor alt'>ᗕ <b>Sensory Overload</b> (psychic, teleportation) ✦ Recharge ⚄ ⚅</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Attack:</i> Close burst 5 (enemies in the burst); +27 vs. Will</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Hit:</i> 2d8 + 6 psychic damage, and the target is blinded and deafened until the end of the elder brain's next turn. The elder brain then teleports the target 3 squares.</p><h2>Triggered Actions</h2><p class='flavor alt'> <b>Baleful Transfer</b> ✦ <b>At-Will</b></p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Trigger:</i> The elder brain saves against an effect.</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Effect (No Action):</i> An enemy within 5 squares of the elder brain is subjected to the same effect the elder brain saved against (save ends).</p><p class='flavor alt'><b>Skills</b> Arcana +25, Bluff +24, Diplomacy +24, Dungeoneering +24<br> <b>Str</b> 23 (+17)                <b>Dex</b> 23 (+17)                <b>Wis</b> 26 (+19)<br><b>Con</b> 26 (+19)                <b>Int</b> 28 (+20)                <b>Cha</b> 27 (+19)</p><p class=flavor><b>Alignment</b> evil       <b> Languages</b> Deep Speech, telepathy 50</p><p class=publishedIn>Published in Monster Manual 3, page(s) 139, Dungeon Magazine 201.</p>",
    "monster3648": "<h1 class=monster>Emperor Zetch'r'r<br><span class=type>Medium natural humanoid githyanki , githyanki</span><br><span class=level>Level 23 Elite Soldier (Leader)<span class=xp> XP 10200</span></span> </h1> <p class=flavor><b>Initiative</b> +15        <b>Senses</b> Perception +18<br><b>Despair</b> (Fear) aura 1; any enemy within the aura takes a −2 penalty to all defenses and saving throws.<br><b>HP</b> 428; <b>Bloodied</b> 214<br><b>AC</b> 39; <b>Fortitude</b> 36, <b>Reflex</b> 32, <b>Will</b> 36<br><b>Saving Throws</b> +2<br><b>Speed</b> 6<br><b>Action Points</b> 1</p><p class='flavor alt'>(⚔) <b>Silver Sword</b> (standard, at-will) ✦ <b>Psychic, Weapon</b></p><p class=flavorIndent>+30 vs AC; 2d6 + 6 damage plus 2d6 psychic damage, and the target is marked until the end of Zetch'r'r's next turn. Against an immobilized target, this attack deals 4d6 extra damage and slides the target 2 squares. </p><p class='flavor alt'>⚔ <b>Double Attack</b> (standard, at-will) ✦ <b>Psychic, Weapon</b></p><p class=flavorIndent>Zetch'r'r makes a silver sword attack against two different targets. </p><p class='flavor alt'>⚔ <b>Parrying Maneuver</b> (standard; requires silver sword, at-will) ✦ <b>Psychic, Weapon</b></p><p class=flavorIndent>Zetch'r'r makes a silver sword attack; on a hit, the target also grants combat advantage to Zetch'r'r until the end of his next turn. </p><p class='flavor alt'>➶ <b>Folded Space</b> (move, encounter) ✦ <b>Teleportation</b></p><p class=flavorIndent>Ranged 5; no attack roll; Zetch'r'r and the target swap spaces. </p><p class='flavor alt'>➶ <b>Telekinetic Vise</b> (standard, recharges when first bloodied) </p><p class=flavorIndent>Ranged 5; +28 vs Fortitude; 2d10 + 8 damage, and the target is immobilized (save ends). </p><p class='flavor alt'>ᗕ <b>Telekinetic Thrust</b> (standard, recharge ⚃⚄⚅) </p><p class=flavorIndent>Close burst 1; targets enemies; +28 vs Fortitude; the target is pushed 1 square and is immobilized (save ends). Miss: The target is pushed 1 square. </p><p class='flavor alt'> <b>Combat Advantage</b></p><p class=flavorIndent>Emperor Zetch'r'r's melee attacks deal 4d6 extra damage against any target granting combat advantage to him.</p><p class='flavor alt'><b>Alignment</b> Evil       <b> Languages</b> Common, Deep Speech, Draconic<br><b>Skills</b> Diplomacy +23, History +18, Insight +18, Intimidate +23<br><b>Str</b> 27 (+19)      <b>Dex</b> 15 (+13)      <b>Wis</b> 14 (+13)<br><b>Con</b> 22 (+17)      <b>Int</b> 21 (+16)      <b>Cha</b> 24 (+18)</p><p class='flavor alt'><b>Equipment</b>: two silver swords, scepter of Ephelomon, plate armor .</p><br><p class=publishedIn>Published in Dungeon Magazine 168, page(s) 92.</p>",
    "monster3008": "<h1 class=monster>Human Insane Noble<br><span class=type>Medium natural humanoid human , human</span><br><span class=level>Level 23 Elite Skirmisher<span class=xp> XP 10200</span></span> </h1> <p class=flavor><b>Initiative</b> +19        <b>Senses</b> Perception +11<br><b>HP</b> 428; <b>Bloodied</b> 214<br><b>AC</b> 37; <b>Fortitude</b> 35, <b>Reflex</b> 35, <b>Will</b> 36<br><b>Saving Throws</b> +2<br><b>Speed</b> 6<br><b>Action Points</b> 1</p><p class='flavor alt'>(⚔) <b>Scepter</b> (standard, at-will) ✦ <b>Weapon</b></p><p class=flavorIndent>+28 vs AC; 3d8+6 damage. </p><p class='flavor alt'>⚔ <b>Flurry of Madness</b> (standard, at-will) </p><p class=flavorIndent>The insane noble shifts 6 squares and makes one scepter attack against each enemy it moves adjacent to.</p><p class='flavor alt'>ᗕ <b>Ignoble Fury</b> (immediate reaction, when first bloodied, ) ✦ <b>Weapon</b></p><p class=flavorIndent>Close burst 1; targets enemies; +26 vs AC; 3d8+6 damage, and the target is knocked prone. </p><p class='flavor alt'> <b>Sheer Madness</b></p><p class=flavorIndent>An insane noble does not provoke opportunity attacks.</p><p class='flavor alt'><b>Alignment</b> Chaotic evil       <b> Languages</b> Common<br><b>Str</b> 16 (+14)      <b>Dex</b> 22 (+17)      <b>Wis</b> 11 (+11)<br><b>Con</b> 22 (+17)      <b>Int</b> 15 (+13)      <b>Cha</b> 24 (+18)</p><p class='flavor alt'><b>Equipment</b>: scepter (mace)</p><br><p class=publishedIn>Published in Monster Manual 2, page(s) 146.</p>",
